"Abstract This conference was a culmination of several years of research under the auspices of the Law Commission of Canada (LCC) 1 focusing on the complicated relationship between public police forces and private security agencies, and followed the publication of the LCC’s Discussion paper In Search of Security: The Roles of Public Police and Private Agencies . 2 This note aims to give our readers a sense of the atmosphere of the conference, and to spark interest in the content and entice them to look at the abstracts, 3 or papers when they are published."
